-- Regression: SYM_TYPE->decl_node blind cast to Iron_ObjectDecl.
--
-- **Motivating Incident.** Phase 65 AUDIT-01 ranks 5 and 6 flagged two
-- sites in src/analyzer/typecheck.c (CALL handler and CONSTRUCT handler)
-- that cast (Iron_ObjectDecl *)sym->decl_node whenever
-- sym->sym_kind == IRON_SYM_TYPE without first checking decl_node->kind.
-- SYM_TYPE symbols can point to Iron_InterfaceDecl, Iron_EnumDecl, or be
-- NULL for builtin primitive types created with decl_node=NULL. The cast
-- silently read wrong memory when the symbol was interface/enum and
-- NULL-deref'd for builtins, producing wrong arity checks that leaked
-- wrong codegen into emitted programs.
--
-- **Layout Diagram.**
--   Iron_ObjectDecl:    { span, kind, name, fields[], field_count, extends_name, ... }
--   Iron_InterfaceDecl: { span, kind, name, method_sigs[], method_count, ... }
--   Iron_EnumDecl:      { span, kind, name, variants[], variant_count, ... }
--   Builtin primitive:  decl_node == NULL
--
--   Reading od->field_count at the InterfaceDecl::method_count offset or
--   the EnumDecl::variant_count offset produced silently-wrong arity checks.
--
-- **Fix Summary.** typecheck.c CALL and CONSTRUCT handlers now check
-- decl_node->kind == IRON_NODE_OBJECT_DECL explicitly, emit a diagnostic
-- for the non-object SYM_TYPE case, and call IRON_NODE_ASSERT_KIND before
-- the cast so Debug builds abort via iron_ice rather than silently
-- misreading memory. PROT-04, Phase 66 Plan 03.
--
-- **Severity.** H. Blast radius: every user program that references an
-- object type in constructor position. Silent memory misinterpretation
-- for interface/enum misuse, possible NULL deref for builtin misuse.

object Circle {
    val radius: Int
}

func area(c: Circle) -> Int {
    return c.radius * c.radius * 3
}

func main() {
    val c = Circle(5)
    println("radius: {c.radius}")
    println("area: {area(c)}")
}
